  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (v0.5 synthetic)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The power-law hemolysis accumulation model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is applied under the theoretical precondition that the scalar stress–exposure relationship is linear and additive across Lagrangian fluid pathlines — an assumption validated at a single nominal operating point (3.5 L/min, 2500 RPM) but not verified across the full five flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
