      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2 for this factor. Simulation team has documented training records and peer-review procedures that provide sufficient assurance without formal use-error quantification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model are appropriate for the flow regime and have published validation evidence for rotary blood pumps.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence closure is selected based on published evidence of superior performance in swirling, recirculating pump flows. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the industry-standard constitutive relation for CFD hemolysis prediction and is cited in FDA guidance. The model applies under the theoretical precondition that instantaneous scalar shear stress accumulates linearly along pathlines — a condition satisfied in the low-to-moderate stress regime characteristic of the nominal validation point. Published literature (Taskin et al., 2012; Hariharan et al., 2015) confirms model adequacy within the stress range 0–400 Pa·s^0.785; the high-speed COU point may exceed this range, but this is not evaluated herein."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Geometric dimensions, fluid properties, and boundary conditions are specified with documented uncertainty ≤ 5% for each input.",
      "rationale": "CAD geometry was measured against the FDA benchmark drawing with dimensional uncertainty < 0.5%. Blood analogue viscosity was characterised at 37°C with ±1.2% uncertainty. Inlet velocity profiles were derived from fully developed pipe flow assumptions verified at the inlet duct length-to-diameter ratio of 18. All model inputs are within the 5% uncertainty threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Formal test sample characterisation beyond standard batch documentation is not required at MRL 2. Blood analogue batches were prepared per ASTM F1841 protocol with viscosity verification."
    },
